    "csaf_version": "2.0",
    "notes": [
      {
        "category": "summary",
        "text": "An update is available for libsoup.\nThis update affects Rocky Linux 9.\nA Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVE list",
        "title": "Topic"
      },
      {
        "category": "description",
        "text": "The libsoup packages provide an HTTP client and server library for GNOME.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* libsoup: Integer Overflow in Cookie Expiration Date Handling in libsoup (CVE-2025-4945)\n\n* libsoup: Out-of-Bounds Read in Cookie Date Handling of libsoup HTTP Library (CVE-2025-11021)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.\n\nThis advisory is provided by Ctrl IQ, Inc for Rocky Linux systems. For more information about CIQ security practices, visit https://ciq.com/security.",
        "title": "Description"
      }
    ],
